Wash and dry produce. Place @Standard Meat Pulled Pork{8%ounce} in a medium
#microwave-safe bowl{}. Using two forks, shred into smaller pieces. Add
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, half the @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce} (all
for 4 servings), and @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste; stir to combine. Cover
with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{2%minutes}. Set aside until ready to
use.

Quarter @Lime{1}. In a second medium #bowl{}, combine @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce},
@Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp sugar for 4 servings),
juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4), and a pinch of @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Lay tortillas on a clean work surface. Spread
@Guacamole{4%tablespoon} on bottom third of tortillas. Top with Southwest
pulled pork, @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}, and as much slaw as you like.
Fold bottom side of each tortilla up over filling, then fold over left and
right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled
sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with remaining lime
wedges and any remaining slaw on the side.

> Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.